line_1: You know, a certain Lady, Dick,
line_2: Who saw Me, when I last was sick:

line_1: Here with an artful Smile, quoth Dick,
line_2: Your Proofs come mighty full, and thick —

line_1: Here hold a Blow, good Friend, quoth Dick,
line_2: And rais'd his Voice exceeding quick:

line_1: From La Fontaine; an Author, Dick,
line_2: Whose Muse would touch thee to the quick.

line_1: Nor batter'd Skull of wrestling Dick,
line_2: Who late was drubb'd at single Stick;

line_1: I little thought that honest Dick
line_2: Would slight me so, when I was sick.

line_1: With gloves and hat, like my own footman, Dick.
line_2: I'd walk the morning with an oaken stick,

line_1: In short so provoking a devil was Dick,
line_2: That we wish'd him full ten times a day at Old Nick.

line_1: Behind the Elmes, last Night, cry'd Dick,
line_2: Rose, were You not extreamly Sick?
